                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-06-11</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>If you are considering or committed to the way of nonviolence and searching for firm footing in the actual practice of peace and reconciliation, read this book.  As always, Wink is challenging, creative, convincing, and compelling.  The many stories he tells to illustrate his points are quite interesting and practical.  <br>This is vintage Wink at his best.  I will refer to this little book often.  It would be a steal at twice the price.</span>
                  
              
